docs.text: get carter -- the latest masterpiece from uber-thespian sylvester stallone -- is a prime example of large and in charge 80's action stars trying to fit back into action roles they have long since outgrown .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: stallone seems like that one uncle you have who tries to be cool with his members only jacket and izod polo shirt with the collar popped up .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a few years ago , stallone made a movie that gave him the opportunity to gracefully exit the roles that typecast him as an action monkey .

docs.text: that role was sheriff freddy heflin in copland -- a strange film about redemption within a broken soul .

docs.text: stallone actually gave an amazing performance and it seemed he had shaken off the past .

docs.text: too bad get carter returns stallone to action , but with the shiny paint rusted off on the edges .

docs.text: get carter is a simple story .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: stallone plays frank carter , a vegas bruiser for a loan shark ( played with amazing gusto by the uncredited voice of actor tom sizemore ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when frank's brother gets himself killed in a drunk driving accident , frank , feeling all guilty and mushy inside , thinks foul play is involved and travels to seattle to set right all the wrongs with the patented " carter's way " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he talks tough with his brother's wife , lends a helping had to his brother's daughter doreen ( rachel leigh cook ) , and walks around seattle in the pouring rain dressed like a lost member of the rat pack with a really bad goatee .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: carter finds out that his brother was involved in some bad stuff with a slimy porn king played by ultra-cool , mcqueen-esque mickey rourke , a multi-millionaire computer geek ( alan cumming ) , and a strange foreign guy ( michael caine ) who speaks in riddles and talks tough .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: carter stalks all of them while trying to figure out who did in his brother and how to extract proper revenge on the responsible parties .

docs.text: actually , get carter is a remake of the 1971 british production of the same name , starring caine in the title role ( and what with his cameo here , the cleverness is astonishing ) .

docs.text: while stallone still carries his own weight here , the movie lacks what the original did as well : purpose .

docs.text: throughout the film , stallone looks like an old guy trying to act tough , while nobody is taking him seriously .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: his one-liners fall flat , and he seems tired and uncertain of all the actions , mental and physical , required of his character .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there is even a strange homoeroticism between rourke and stallone that lends a bizarre tone to their numerous conversations -- in both fists and words .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the biggest surprise in get carter is that the best job done in the film is by the versatile mickey rourke .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: an amazing method actor in the eighties who fell into drugs , spousal abuse , a boxing career , and an intolerable attitude towards not getting his way , rourke still brings a dangerous sense of purpose to his porn king character .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he may not win any oscars , but he still ranks highly in my book .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: get carter has great directing , strong acting by rourke and caine , and energetic car chases that would make william friedkin proud .

docs.text: the only thing it lacks - as with most hollywood productions -- is a good script and proper casting .
